HEADWORD: Covenanter
<hw>Cov"e*nant*er</hw> <pr>(k?v"?-n?nt-?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who makes a covenant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One who subscribed and
defended the ⟦ldquo⟧Solemn League and Covenant.⟦rdquo⟧ See
<er>Covenant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Covenanting</ent>⟦br⟧
